      { question: "The nurse is administering IV calcium gluconate to a patient in celiac crisis. Which nursing action is essential?", options: ["Push the medication rapidly to correct the deficit quickly", "Administer via peripheral IV in a large vein and monitor cardiac rhythm during infusion", "Mix with IV potassium in the same bag for efficiency", "Administer regardless of concurrent magnesium levels"], correct: 1, rationale: "IV calcium must be administered slowly (over 10-20 minutes) with continuous cardiac monitoring as rapid infusion can cause bradycardia or cardiac arrest. Extravasation of calcium causes severe tissue necrosis." }
